Potent activator of the human ion channels transient receptor potential V3 (TRPV3) and A1 (TRPA1). It has a role as a volatile oil component, a flavouring agent, an antimicrobial agent, an agrochemical and a TRPA1 channel agonist. It is a member of phenols, a p-menthane monoterpenoid and a botanical anti-fungal agent. It derives from a hydride of a p-cymene.

It is a long-chain fatty acid and a straight-chain saturated fatty acid. It is a conjugate acid of a hexadecanoate.

Name: PENTADECANAL
Description: Pentadecanal is a long-chain fatty aldehyde that is pentadecane carrying an oxo substituent at position 1. It is a component of essential oils from plants like Solanum erianthum and Cassia siamea. It has a role as an antimicrobial agent, a volatile oil component and a plant metabolite. It is a long-chain fatty aldehyde and a 2,3-saturated fatty aldehyde.

Name: 1,4-dihydroxy-2-methoxy-7-methylanthraquinone
Description: 1,4-Dihydroxy-3-methoxy-6-methylanthraquinone has been reported in Cortinarius persplendidus, Nigrospora, and Fusarium with data available.

Name: 1,6-Dihydroxy-2,4-dimethoxyanthraquinone
Description: from Morinda officinalis; structure given in first source

Name: 1,6-Dihydroxy-2-methoxyanthraquinone
Description: from Morinda officinalis; structure given in first source

Name: 1,6-DIHYDROXY-5-METHOXY-2-(METHOXYMETHYL)ANTHRACENE-9,10-DIONE
Description: 9,10-Anthracenedione, 1,6-dihydroxy-5-methoxy-2-(methoxymethyl)- has been reported in Morinda citrifolia with data available.

Name: 1-hydroxy-2,3-dimethylanthracene-9,10-dione
Description: 1-Hydroxy-2,3-dimethylanthracene-9,10-dione has been reported in Gynochthodes officinalis with data available.

Description: 1-hydroxy-2-methyl-9,10-anthraquinone is a member of the class of hydroxyanthraquinones that is anthracene-9,10-dione substituted by a hydroxy group at position 1 and a methyl group at position 2. It has been isolated from the roots of Rubia yunnanensis. It has a role as a plant metabolite.
1-Hydroxy-3-methoxyanthracene-9,10-dione has been reported in Rubia wallichiana and Rubia tinctorum with data available.

Name: 9,10-Anthracenedione, 1-hydroxy-3-(hydroxmethyl)-

Name: 2-HYDROXY-1,5-DIMETHOXY-6-(METHOXYMETHYL)ANTHRACENE-9,10-DIONE
Description: 1,5,15-Tri-O-methylmorindol has been reported in Morinda citrifolia with data available.

It has been isolated from the roots of Rubia yunnanensis. It has a role as an antineoplastic agent and a plant metabolite. It is a primary alcohol and a monohydroxyanthraquinone.

Name: 2-Hydroxy-3-methylanthraquinone
Description: 2-Hydroxy-3-methylanthraquinone has been reported in Oldenlandia herbacea var. herbacea, Oldenlandia diffusa, and other organisms with data available.

Name: 2-HYDROXYANTHRAQUINONE
Description: 2-hydroxyanthraquinone is a monohydroxyanthraquinone.

Name: Pentadecan-2-one
Description: 2-Pentadecanone is a ketone.

Name: 2-PHENYLDODECANE
Description: 2-Phenyldodecane has been reported in Acca sellowiana with data available.

Name: 2-Undecanone
Description: Undecan-2-one is a dialkyl ketone with methyl and nonyl as the two alkyl groups. It has a role as a rodenticide and a plant metabolite. It is a dialkyl ketone and a methyl ketone.

Name: 3,8-Dimethylundecane
Description: 3,8-dimethylundecane is an alkane that is undecane substituted by methyl groups at positions 3 and 8. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism. It has a role as a human metabolite. It derives from a hydride of an undecane.

Description: 4-[3-(Hydroxymethyl)-6-(3-hydroxyprop-1-enyl)-2,3-dihydro-1,4-benzodioxin-2-yl]benzene-1,2-diol has been reported in Capparis with data available.

Name: 5-(1-hydroxyethyl)oxolan-2-one
Description: Sherry lactone is a gamma-lactone.

Name: exo-2-Hydroxycineole
Description: 2-Hydroxycineol is a member of oxanes.

Name: Alizarin 1-methyl ether
Description: Alizarin 1-methyl ether has been reported in Oldenlandia herbacea var. herbacea, Rubia wallichiana, and other organisms with data available.

Name: 1-Hydroxy-2-methoxyanthraquinone
Description: Alizarin 2-methyl ether is an anthraquinone.
1,2,4a,5,6,8a-Hexahydro-1-isopropyl-4,7-dimethylnaphthalene has been reported in Callistemon citrinus, Humulus lupulus, and other organisms with data available.

Name: alpha-Curcumene
Description: Alpha-curcumene is a sesquiterpene that is 2-methyl-2-heptene in which one of the hydrogens at position 6 is substituted by a p-tolyl group.

Name: 2-Hepten-1-al
Description: 2-Hepten-1-al has been reported in Punica granatum, Aloe africana, and other organisms with data available.

Name: ALPHA-PINENE
Description: Alpha-pinene appears as a clear colorless liquid with a turpentine odor. Flash point 91 °F. Less dense than water and insoluble in water. Vapors are heavier than air. Used as a solvent.

Name: alpha-TERPINEOL
Description: Alpha-terpineol is a terpineol that is propan-2-ol substituted by a 4-methylcyclohex-3-en-1-yl group at position 2. It has a role as a plant metabolite.
3-[2-(3,4-Dihydroxyphenyl)-3-(hydroxymethyl)-2,3-dihydro-1,4-benzodioxin-6-yl]prop-2-enal has been reported in Amblyomma americanum with data available.

Name: Arachidic acid
Description: Icosanoic acid is a C20 striaght-chain saturated fatty acid which forms a minor constituent of peanut (L. arachis) and corn oils. Used as an organic thin film in the production of liquid crystals for a wide variety of technical applications. It has a role as a plant metabolite. It is a straight-chain saturated fatty acid and a long-chain fatty acid. It is a conjugate acid of an icosanoate.

Name: Record Description
Description: [5-(hexopyranosyloxy)-1-oxo-2a,4a,5,7b-tetrahydro-1H-2,6-dioxacyclopenta[cd]inden-4-yl]methyl acetate has been reported in Oldenlandia herbacea var. herbacea, Paederia scandens, and other organisms with data available.

Name: 7-(Acetyloxymethyl)-5-hydroxy-1-[3,4,5-trihydroxy-6-(hydroxymethyl)oxan-2-yl]oxy-1,4a,5,7a-tetrahydrocyclopenta[c]pyran-4-carboxylic acid
Description: 7-(Acetyloxymethyl)-5-hydroxy-1-[3,4,5-trihydroxy-6-(hydroxymethyl)oxan-2-yl]oxy-1,4a,5,7a-tetrahydrocyclopenta[c]pyran-4-carboxylic acid has been reported in Globularia punctata, Oldenlandia diffusa, and other organisms with data available.

Name: benzaldehyde
Description: Benzaldehyde appears as a clear colorless to yellow liquid with a bitter almond odor. Flash point near 145 °F. More denser than water and insoluble in water. Hence sinks in water. Vapors are heavier than air. The primary hazard is to the environment. Immediate steps should be taken to limit spread to the environment. Easily penetrates the soil to contaminate groundwater and nearby waterways. Used in flavoring and perfume making.

Name: Sesquiphellandrene
Description: beta-Sesquiphellandrene has been reported in Curcuma kwangsiensis, Curcuma phaeocaulis, and other organisms with data available.

Name: 17-(5-ethyl-6-methylheptan-2-yl)-10,13-dimethyl-2,3,4,7,8,9,11,12,14,15,16,17-dodecahydro-1H-cyclopenta[a]phenanthren-3-ol
Description: 17-(5-ethyl-6-methylheptan-2-yl)-10,13-dimethyl-2,3,4,7,8,9,11,12,14,15,16,17-dodecahydro-1H-cyclopenta[a]phenanthren-3-ol has been reported in Euphorbia prostrata, Otanthus maritimus, and other organisms with data available.

Name: Borneol
Description: Borneol appears as a white colored lump-solid with a sharp camphor-like odor. Burns readily. Slightly denser than water and insoluble in water. Used to make perfumes.

Name: 2,6-Di-tert-butyl-4-methylphenol
Description: Butylated hydroxytoluene is a white crystalline solid. (NTP, 1992)

Name: 3-(3,4-dihydroxyphenyl)prop-2-enoic acid
Description: 3,4-Dihydroxy cinnamic acid has been reported in Salvia miltiorrhiza, Acanthospermum australe, and other organisms with data available.

Name: octanoic acid
Description: Octanoic acid appears as a colorless to light yellow liquid with a mild odor. Burns, but may be difficult to ignite. Corrosive to metals and tissue.

Name: Cedran-8-ol
Description: Cedran-8-ol has been reported in Artemisia annua, Chamaecyparis obtusa var. formosana, and other organisms with data available.

Name: 1-Hexadecene
Description: 1-hexadecene is an unbranched sixteen-carbon alkene with one double bond between C-1 and C-2.

Name: citric acid
Description: Citric acid appears as colorless, odorless crystals with an acid taste. Denser than water. (USCG, 1999)

Name: P-CYMENE
Description: P-cymene is a colorless liquid with a mild pleasant odor. Floats on water. (USCG, 1999)

Name: Record Description
Description: 6-(Hydroxymethyl)-8-[3,4,5-trihydroxy-6-(hydroxymethyl)oxan-2-yl]oxy-3,9-dioxatricyclo[5.3.1.04,11]undeca-1(10),5-dien-2-one has been reported in Paederia scandens, Paederia foetida, and Oldenlandia diffusa with data available.

Name: Digiferruginol
Description: Digiferrugineol is an anthraquinone.

Name: DESACETYL ASPERULOSIDIC ACID
Description: Cyclopenta[c]pyran-4-carboxylicacid, 1-(b-D-glucopyranosyloxy)-1,4a,5,7a-tetrahydro-5-hydroxy-7-(hydroxymethyl)-,(1S,4aS,5S,7aS)- has been reported in Paederia scandens, Globularia punctata, and other organisms with data available.

Name: dibutyl phthalate
Description: Di-n-phtalate is a manufactured chemical that does not occur naturally. It is an odorless and oily liquid that is colorless to faint yellow in color. It is slightly soluble in water and does not evaporate easily. Di-n-phtalate is used to make plastics more flexible and is also in carpet backings, paints, glue, insect repellents, hair spray, nail polish, and rocket fuel.

Name: DODECANE
Description: N-dodecane is a clear colorless liquid. (NTP, 1992)

Name: 9,12-Octadecadienoic acid
Description: 9,12-Octadecadienoic acid has been reported in Arisaema tortuosum, Humulus lupulus, and other organisms with data available.

Name: Esculetin
Description: Esculetin is a hydroxycoumarin that is umbelliferone in which the hydrogen at position 6 is substituted by a hydroxy group. It is used in filters for absorption of ultraviolet light. It has a role as an antioxidant, an ultraviolet filter and a plant metabolite.

Name: DIETHYL ETHER
Description: Diethyl ether appears as a clear colorless liquid with an anesthetic odor. Flash point -49 °F. Less dense than water and slightly soluble in water. Hence floats on water. Vapors are heavier than air. Used as a solvent and to make other chemicals.

Name: ethyl octadec-9-enoate
Description: Ethyl octadec-9-enoate has been reported in Aristolochia grandiflora, Cinnamomum camphora, and other organisms with data available.

Name: ETHYL PALMITATE
Description: Ethyl hexadecanoate is a long-chain fatty acid ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of palmitic acid with the hydroxy group of ethanol. It has a role as a plant metabolite. It is a hexadecanoate ester and a long-chain fatty acid ethyl ester.

Name: ETHYL PENTADECANOATE
Description: Ethyl pentadecanoate is a fatty acid ester.

Name: Gamma-undecalactone
Description: Xi-gamma-Undecalactone is a lactone.

Name: 3,7-Dimethyl-2,6-octadienol
Description: 3,7-Dimethyl-2,6-octadien-1-ol has been reported in Cymbopogon martinii, Eremothecium ashbyi, and other organisms with data available.

Name: 1-methyl-4-prop-1-en-2-ylcyclohexene
Description: Dipentene appears as a colorless liquid with an odor of lemon. Flash point 113 °F. Density about 7.2 lb /gal and insoluble in water. Hence floats on water. Vapors heavier than air. Used as a solvent for rosin, waxes, rubber; as a dispersing agent for oils, resins, paints, lacquers, varnishes, and in floor waxes and furniture polishes.

Name: HEPTADECANE
Description: Hexagonal leafs. (NTP, 1992)

Name: HEXANOIC ACID
Description: Caproic acid appears as a white crystalline solid or colorless to light yellow solution with an unpleasant odor. Insoluble to slightly soluble in water and less dense than water. Contact may severely irritate skin, eyes and mucous membranes. May be toxic by ingestion, inhalation and skin absorption. Used to make perfumes.

Name: phenylacetaldehyde
Description: Phenylacetaldehyde is an aldehyde that consists of acetaldehyde bearing a methyl substituent; the parent member of the phenylacetaldehyde class of compounds. It has a role as a human metabolite, a Saccharomyces cerevisiae metabolite, an Escherichia coli metabolite and a mouse metabolite. It is an alpha-CH2-containing aldehyde and a member of phenylacetaldehydes.

Name: 1-HYDROXYANTHRAQUINONE
Description: 1-Hydroxyanthraquinone can cause cancer according to California Labor Code.

Name: 7-hexadecenoic acid
Description: 7-Hexadecenoic acid has been reported in Monascus purpureus and Mangifera indica with data available.

Name: indole
Description: 1H-indole is an indole and a polycyclic heteroarene. It has a role as an Escherichia coli metabolite. It is a tautomer of a 3H-indole.

Name: Isofraxidin
Description: Isofraxidin is a hydroxycoumarin.

Name: Record Description
Description: 4-[6-[2-(3,4-Dihydroxyphenyl)-3-(hydroxymethyl)-2,3-dihydro-1,4-benzodioxin-6-yl]-1,3,3a,4,6,6a-hexahydrofuro[3,4-c]furan-3-yl]benzene-1,2-diol has been reported in Morinda citrifolia with data available.

Name: ISOPHORONE
Description: Isophorone is a clear liquid that smells like peppermint. It can be dissolved in water and evaporates somewhat faster than water. It is an industrial chemical used as a solvent in some printing inks, paints, lacquers, and adhesives. It is also used as an intermediate in the production of certain chemicals. Although isophorone is an industrial chemical, it also occurs naturally in cranberries.

Name: alpha-TERPINEOL
Description: Alpha-terpineol is a terpineol that is propan-2-ol substituted by a 4-methylcyclohex-3-en-1-yl group at position 2. It has a role as a plant metabolite.

Name: lauric acid
Description: Lauric acid is a white solid with a slight odor of bay oil. (USCG, 1999)

Name: Record Description
Description: Bornyl acetate is an organic molecular entity. It has a role as a flavouring agent and a fragrance.

Name: Linalool
Description: Linalool is a monoterpenoid that is octa-1,6-diene substituted by methyl groups at positions 3 and 7 and a hydroxy group at position 3. It has been isolated from plants like Ocimum canum. It has a role as a plant metabolite, a volatile oil component, an antimicrobial agent and a fragrance. It is a tertiary alcohol and a monoterpenoid.
an important fragrance allergen; RN and structure in first source

Name: 2-carbomethoxy-9,10-anthraquinone
Description: 2-carbomethoxy-9,10-anthraquinone is an anthraquinone that is 9,10-anthraquinone substituted by a methoxycarbonyl group at position 2. It has been isolated from the roots of Rubia yunnanensis. It has a role as a plant metabolite. It is an anthraquinone, an aromatic ester and a methyl ester.

Name: 2-METHYLBENZOFURAN
Description: 2-Methylcumarone is a member of benzofurans.

Name: METHYL HEPTADECANOATE
Description: Methyl heptadecanoate is a fatty acid methyl ester.

Name: Monotropeine
Description: Monotropeine has been reported in Galium rivale, Pyrola japonica, and other organisms with data available.

Name: Morindacin
Description: Morindacin has been reported in Oldenlandia diffusa with data available.

Name: Morindone
Description: Morindone is a trihydroxyanthraquinone.

Name: 3-Methylbenzaldehyde
Description: M-tolualdehyde is a tolualdehyde compound with the methyl substituent at the 3-position. It has a role as a plant metabolite.

Name: Tetradecanoic acid
Description: Tetradecanoic acid is an oily white crystalline solid. (NTP, 1992)

Name: Heptanal
Description: N-heptaldehyde appears as a colorless, oily liquid with a penetrating fruity odor. Insoluble in water and less dense than water. Hence floats on water. Used to make perfumes and pharmaceuticals.

Name: Decanoic acid
Description: Decanoic acid is a white crystalline solid with a rancid odor. Melting point 31.5 °C. Soluble in most organic solvents and in dilute nitric acid; non-toxic. Used to make esters for perfumes and fruit flavors and as an intermediate for food-grade additives.

Name: NONANAL
Description: Nonanal is a clear brown liquid characterized by a rose-orange odor. Insoluble in water. Found in at least 20 essential oils, including rose and citrus oils and several species of pine oil.

Name: NONANOIC ACID
Description: Nonanoic acid is a C9 straight-chain saturated fatty acid which occurs naturally as esters of the oil of pelargonium. Has antifungal properties, and is also used as a herbicide as well as in the preparation of plasticisers and lacquers. It has a role as an antifeedant, a plant metabolite, a Daphnia magna metabolite and an algal metabolite. It is a straight-chain saturated fatty acid and a medium-chain fatty acid. It is a conjugate acid of a nonanoate. It derives from a hydride of a nonane.

Name: Neopentyl glycol
Description: 2,2-dimethylpropane-1,3-diol is a white crystalline solid. Melting point 130 °C.

Name: 1-octanol
Description: Octanol appears as a clear colorless liquid with a penetrating aromatic odor. Insoluble in water and floats on water. Vapors heavier than air. Vapors may irritate the eyes, nose, and respiratory system.

Name: oct-2-enal
Description: Oct-2-enal has been reported in Pternistria bispina, Gossypium hirsutum, and other organisms with data available.

Name: OCTADECANE
Description: N-octadecane is a colorless liquid. (NTP, 1992)

Name: 9-octadecenoic acid
Description: 9-Octadecenoic acid has been reported in Pongamia pinnata var. pinnata, Arisaema tortuosum, and other organisms with data available.

Name: methanol
Description: Methanol can cause developmental toxicity according to The National Toxicology Program.

Name: Octanal
Description: N-octylaldehyde is a colorless liquids with a strong fruity odor. Less dense than water and insoluble in water. Flash points 125 °F. Used in making perfumes and flavorings.

Name: palmitic acid
Description: Hexadecanoic acid is a straight-chain, sixteen-carbon, saturated long-chain fatty acid. It has a role as an EC 1.1.1.189 (prostaglandin-E2 9-reductase) inhibitor, a plant metabolite, a Daphnia magna metabolite and an algal metabolite. It is a long-chain fatty acid and a straight-chain saturated fatty acid. It is a conjugate acid of a hexadecanoate.

Name: N-PHENYL-1-NAPHTHYLAMINE
Description: N-phenyl-1-naphthylamine appears as white to slightly yellowish prisms or reddish brown crystalline powder. (NTP, 1992)

Name: 2-PHENYLETHANOL
Description: 2-phenylethanol is a primary alcohol that is ethanol substituted by a phenyl group at position 2. It has a role as a fragrance, a Saccharomyces cerevisiae metabolite, a plant metabolite, an Aspergillus metabolite and a plant growth retardant. It is a primary alcohol and a member of benzenes.

Name: PENTADECANOIC ACID
Description: Pentadecanoic acid is a straight-chain saturated fatty acid containing fifteen-carbon atoms. It has a role as a plant metabolite, a food component, a Daphnia magna metabolite, a human blood serum metabolite and an algal metabolite. It is a long-chain fatty acid and a straight-chain saturated fatty acid. It is a conjugate acid of a pentadecanoate.

Name: 2-PENTYLFURAN
Description: 2-pentylfuran is a member of the class of furans that is furan in which the hydrogen at position 2 is replaced by a pentyl group. It is found in many heat-processed foods and drinks. It has a role as an Aspergillus metabolite, a human urinary metabolite, a volatile oil component, an insect repellent, a flavouring agent, a plant growth stimulator and a bacterial metabolite.

Name: PHENANTHRENE
Description: Phenanthrene appears as colorless monoclinic crystals with a faint aromatic odor. Solutions exhibit a blue fluorescence. (NTP, 1992)

Name: Physcion
Description: Physcion is a dihydroxyanthraquinone that is 9,10-anthraquinone bearing hydroxy substituents at positions 1 and 8, a methoxy group at position 3, and a methyl group at position 6. It has been widely isolated and characterised from both terrestrial and marine sources. It has a role as an apoptosis inducer, an antineoplastic agent, a hepatoprotective agent, an anti-inflammatory agent, an antibacterial agent, an antifungal agent and a metabolite. It is functionally related to a 2-methylanthraquinone.

Name: piperidine-2-carboxylic acid
Description: Pipecolic acid is a piperidinemonocarboxylic acid in which the carboxy group is located at position C-2. It is a conjugate acid of a pipecolate.

Name: hexadecanal
Description: Hexadecanal is a long-chain fatty aldehyde and a 2,3-saturated fatty aldehyde. It has a role as a human metabolite, a Saccharomyces cerevisiae metabolite and a mouse metabolite.

Name: RefChem:742210
Description: Hex-2-ulofuranosyl hexopyranosyl-(1->6)hexopyranoside is an oligosaccharide.

Name: Ilexolic acid
Description: Ilexolic acid A has been reported in Diospyros, Clethra barbinervis, and Ilex rotunda with data available.

Name: Rubiadin
Description: Rubiadin is a dihydroxyanthraquinone that is anthracene-9,10-dione substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 1 and 3 and a methyl group at position 2. It has been isolated from Rubia yunnanensis. It has a role as an antibacterial agent, an antioxidant, a hepatoprotective agent and a plant metabolite.

Name: Rubiadin 1-methyl ether
Description: Rubiadin 1-methyl ether has been reported in Hymenodictyon orixense, Coelospermum paniculatum, and other organisms with data available.
Gamma-nonalactone has been reported in Citrullus lanatus with data available.

Name: camphor
Description: Camphor appears as a colorless or white colored crystalline powder with a strong mothball-like odor. About the same density as water. Emits flammable vapors above 150 °F. Used to make moth proofings, pharmaceuticals, and flavorings.

Name: DESACETYL ASPERULOSIDIC ACID
Description: Cyclopenta[c]pyran-4-carboxylicacid, 1-(b-D-glucopyranosyloxy)-1,4a,5,7a-tetrahydro-5-hydroxy-7-(hydroxymethyl)-,(1S,4aS,5S,7aS)- has been reported in Paederia scandens, Globularia punctata, and other organisms with data available.

Name: scopoletin
Description: Scopoletin is a hydroxycoumarin that is umbelliferone bearing a methoxy substituent at position 6. It has a role as a plant growth regulator and a plant metabolite. It is functionally related to an umbelliferone.

Name: 17-(5-ethyl-6-methylheptan-2-yl)-10,13-dimethyl-2,3,4,7,8,9,11,12,14,15,16,17-dodecahydro-1H-cyclopenta[a]phenanthren-3-ol
Description: 17-(5-ethyl-6-methylheptan-2-yl)-10,13-dimethyl-2,3,4,7,8,9,11,12,14,15,16,17-dodecahydro-1H-cyclopenta[a]phenanthren-3-ol has been reported in Euphorbia prostrata, Otanthus maritimus, and other organisms with data available.
(E,E,E,E)-Squalene has been reported in Erythrophleum fordii, Sideritis candicans, and other organisms with data available.

Name: stachyose hydrate
Description: Stachyose hydrate has been reported in Lens culinaris and Bifidobacterium breve with data available.

Name: stearic acid
Description: Stearic acid is a white solid with a mild odor. Floats on water. (USCG, 1999)

Name: succinic acid
Description: Succinic acid appears as white crystals or shiny white odorless crystalline powder. pH of 0.1 molar solution: 2.7. Very acid taste. (NTP, 1992)

Name: 6-METHYL-5-HEPTEN-2-ONE
Description: Sulcatone is a heptenone that is hept-5-en-2-one substituted by a methyl group at position 6. It is a volatile oil component of citronella oil, lemon-grass oil and palmarosa oil. It has a role as an alarm pheromone, a volatile oil component and a plant metabolite. It is a methyl ketone and a heptenone.

Name: 2-Methylanthraquinone
Description: 2-methylanthraquinone is an anthraquinone that is 9,10-anthraquinone in which the hydrogen at position 2 is substituted by a methyl group. It is functionally related to a 9,10-anthraquinone.

Name: Terpinen-4-ol
Description: 4-terpineol is a terpineol that is 1-menthene carrying a hydroxy substituent at position 4. It has a role as a plant metabolite, an antibacterial agent, an antioxidant, an anti-inflammatory agent, an antiparasitic agent, an antineoplastic agent, an apoptosis inducer and a volatile oil component. It is a terpineol and a tertiary alcohol.

Name: Tetracosanoic acid
Description: Tetracosanoic acid is a C24 straight-chain saturated fatty acid. It has a role as a volatile oil component, a plant metabolite, a human metabolite and a Daphnia tenebrosa metabolite. It is a very long-chain fatty acid and a straight-chain saturated fatty acid. It is a conjugate acid of a tetracosanoate.

Name: Record Description
Description: N-tetradecane is a colorless liquid. Must be preheated before ignition can occur. (NTP, 1992)
Undecenal has been reported in Anthemis aciphylla, Coriandrum sativum, and other organisms with data available.

Name: NONADECANE
Description: Wax. (NTP, 1992)

Name: D-erythro-Hex-2-enonic acid, gamma-lactone

Isolated from Ginkgo biloba and Dioon, it exhibits anti-HSV-1, antineoplastic and inhibitory activities towards arachidonate 5-lipoxygenase and cyclooxygenase 2. It has a role as an anti-HSV-1 agent, a cyclooxygenase 2 inhibitor, an EC 1.13.11.34 (arachidonate 5-lipoxygenase) inhibitor, an antineoplastic agent and a metabolite. It is a biflavonoid, a hydroxyflavone, a methoxyflavone and a ring assembly. It is functionally related to an amentoflavone.

Name: Isorhamnetin
Description: Isorhamnetin is a monomethoxyflavone that is quercetin in which the hydroxy group at position 3' is replaced by a methoxy group. It has a role as an EC 1.14.18.1 (tyrosinase) inhibitor, an anticoagulant and a metabolite. It is a 7-hydroxyflavonol, a tetrahydroxyflavone and a monomethoxyflavone. It is functionally related to a quercetin. It is a conjugate acid of an isorhamnetin(1-).

Name: kaempferol
Description: Kaempferol is a tetrahydroxyflavone in which the four hydroxy groups are located at positions 3, 5, 7 and 4'. Acting as an antioxidant by reducing oxidative stress, it is currently under consideration as a possible cancer treatment. It has a role as an antibacterial agent, a plant metabolite, a human xenobiotic metabolite, a human urinary metabolite, a human blood serum metabolite and a geroprotector. It is a member of flavonols, a 7-hydroxyflavonol and a tetrahydroxyflavone. It is a conjugate acid of a kaempferol oxoanion.

It is an alpha-amino acid and a sulfur-containing amino acid. It is functionally related to a butyric acid. It is a conjugate base of a methioninium. It is a conjugate acid of a methioninate. It is a tautomer of a methionine zwitterion.
